subject: From: Central Bank of Nigeri
body:
From: Central Bank of Nigeria
Plot 33,Abubakar Tafawa Balewa Way
Central Business District,
Federal Capital Territory,
Garki Abuja.
Nigeria
Dear Beneficiary.
This is to officially inform you that Central Bank of Nigeria have
released and approved Your Payment File as a foreign beneficiary who
will finally inherit cash payment of US$19,500,000.00 via United
Nations approved Doorstep delivery.
Instruction was given to CBN by the Federal Government of Nigeria,
through the Federal Ministry of Finance/AUDITS,as mandated by United
Nations (UN) and (IMF) to transfer the approved sum of
US$19,500,000.00 as a Cash delivery to your doorstep in your  country
under U.N Diplomatic coverage tag.
More importantly, The whole fund have been securely packaged in a
consignment beyond any security intervention by the Central Bank Fund
packaging and Logistics Department and will be hand over to a known
expatriate who will deliver the cash to you as a classified diplomatic
pouches to your doorstep in your country under international approved
U.N Diplomatic Immunity coverage tag.
Reply me immediately for effective communication and process of your
Courier delivery to your doorstep within 72hrs.
Reply swiftly to Email: 
drkingsleyobioradgepd@outlook.com
Yours Faithfully
Dr.Kingsley Obiora
Deputy Governor,CBN
Alternate Executive Director (IMF)

subject: Re:   From: Central Bank of Nigeri
body:
Dear Obiora,

Thank you for reaching out to me with this information. I must say, it sounds quite intriguing. I would appreciate it if you could provide me with some more details about the process of the courier delivery to my doorstep. How long does it usually take for the delivery to be completed? Are there any fees or charges associated with this service?

Looking forward to your response.

Best wishes,
Francis
